# Backend Standards

## Language

- Use C# 13 and .NET 9.
- Enable nullable reference types.
- Use implicit usings.

## Entity Framework

- Use EF Core with SQLite.
- All DB access goes through DbContext.
- Use migrations.

## Naming

- Commands end with Command.
- Queries end with Query.
- Handlers end with Handler.
- Validators end with Validator.

## Validation

- Use FluentValidation.
- Validate all commands and queries.

## Error Handling

- Use global exception middleware.
- Return ProblemDetails responses.

## Logging

- Use structured logging.
- Never use Console.WriteLine.

## Async

- Use async/await everywhere.
- Avoid blocking calls.
